1. *Stojiš* na pogrešnom peronu. (You are standing on the wrong platform.)
2. Ne *stojiš* pravilno dok vežbaš. (You are not standing correctly while exercising.)
3. On *stoji* ispred prodavnice. (He is standing in front of the store.)
4. *Stojim* već sat vremena u redu za karte. (I have been standing in line for tickets for an hour.)
5. Da li ti *stoji* ova haljina? (Does this dress look good on you?)
6. Ona *stoji* pored mene na fotografiji. (She is standing next to me in the photo.)
7. Nisam siguran da mi *stoji* ovaj friz. (I'm not sure if this hairstyle suits me.)
8. *Stojimo* na kiši već pola sata. (We have been standing in the rain for half an hour.)
9. *Stojimo* na raskrsnici, ne znam kojim putem da idemo. (We are standing at the intersection, I don't know which way to go.)
10. *Stajalište* je odmah tu iza ugla. (The bus stop is just around the corner.)

Note: The word "stojiš" is only used in the first sentence, as it is the second person singular present tense of the verb "stajati" (to stand). The other forms of the word "stajati" are used in the remaining sentences.